[30;1m734 | [0m[35m    # at runtime, leading to keys of a mix of types _KT and tuple[_KT, _VT].[0m
[30;1m735 | [0m[35m    # We don't currently have any way of forcing all Mappings to use[0m
[30;1m736 | [0m[35m    # the first overload, but by using overloading rather than a Union,[0m
[30;1m737 | [0m[35m    # mypy will commit to using the first overload when the argument is[0m

[30;1m71 | [0m[35m    # `SerialBase` does not define `read` at runtime but REQUIRES subclasses to implement it and[0m
[30;1m72 | [0m[35m    # require it to return `bytes`.[0m
[30;1m73 | [0m[35m    # Abstract:[0m
[30;1m74 | [0m[35m    # ---------[0m

[30;1m48 | [0m[35m### Package versioning for third-party stubs[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mVersion numbers of third-party stub packages consist of at least four parts.[0m
[30;1m51 | [0m[35mAll parts of the stub version, except for the last part, correspond to the[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35mversion of the runtime package being stubbed. For example, if the `types-foo`[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35mpackage has version `1.2.0.20240309`, this guarantees that the `types-foo` package[0m
